1
00:02:23,713 --> 00:02:25,238
<i>Once upon a time,</i>

2
00:02:25,344 --> 00:02:27,387
<i>there was a brave little mouse</i>

3
00:02:27,459 --> 00:02:31,008
<i>who loved honor and justice</i>
<i>and always told the truth.</i>

4
00:02:45,014 --> 00:02:46,673
<i>No, that's not him.</i>

5
00:02:48,314 --> 00:02:49,723
<i>That's a rat.</i>

6
00:02:50,043 --> 00:02:51,123
<i>And anyone who knows anything,</i>

7
00:02:51,196 --> 00:02:53,653
<i>knows there's a big difference</i>
<i>between a mouse and a rat.</i>

8
00:02:53,727 --> 00:02:54,711
Ohhh.

9
00:02:54,976 --> 00:02:57,655
<i>First of all,
rats hate the light.</i>

10
00:03:00,230 --> 00:03:02,720
<i>They spend their
lives in the darkness.</i>

11
00:03:03,048 --> 00:03:04,261
<i>They're also terrified of people,</i>

12
00:03:04,331 --> 00:03:06,372
<i>which is why they slink</i>
<i>and cower all the time.</i>

13
00:03:06,476 --> 00:03:07,460
Ooh!

14
00:03:07,790 --> 00:03:09,898
<i>And as far as telling
the truth is concerned,</i>

15
00:03:10,001 --> 00:03:12,653
<i>well, that's impossible</i>
<i>because, as everyone knows,</i>

16
00:03:14,036 --> 00:03:15,698
<i>a rat can't talk.</i>

17
00:03:15,863 --> 00:03:17,291
Tell me that thing again, please.

18
00:03:17,752 --> 00:03:18,898
Come on.

19
00:03:19,545 --> 00:03:20,792
Just once, I promise.

20
00:03:20,892 --> 00:03:21,940
Tell me one more time,

21
00:03:22,045 --> 00:03:23,639
and I won't ask you ever again. I swear.

22
00:03:24,832 --> 00:03:27,649
Fine. We are headed to Dor,

23
00:03:27,715 --> 00:03:30,401
one of the most
magical places in the whole world.

24
00:03:30,501 --> 00:03:31,966
No, that's not what you said before.

25
00:03:32,040 --> 00:03:34,496
You know, every place
has something special.

26
00:03:34,569 --> 00:03:36,940
And, in Dor, it's the soup!

27
00:03:37,070 --> 00:03:38,695
Land ho!

28
00:03:42,739 --> 00:03:43,721
Ohhh.

29
00:03:44,852 --> 00:03:46,195
It's down below, I tell you.

30
00:03:46,261 --> 00:03:47,244
Give it a heave.

31
00:03:52,156 --> 00:03:53,563
I can see it!

32
00:03:55,904 --> 00:03:59,485
Ooh, I can smell it! I can smell it.

33
00:04:06,539 --> 00:04:08,964
Oh, I can't wait
to taste the soup!

34
00:04:09,262 --> 00:04:10,691
Just stay close.

35
00:04:10,767 --> 00:04:11,979
We leave again at 6:00.

36
00:04:12,049 --> 00:04:14,768
You know, we ought to think
about staying here just a little longer.

37
00:04:14,867 --> 00:04:16,779
Don't even think about it.

38
00:04:17,046 --> 00:04:18,062
Remember Shanghai?

39
00:04:18,135 --> 00:04:19,663
Yeah, but this place is different.

40
00:04:20,057 --> 00:04:21,947
I mean, this is special.

41
00:04:24,381 --> 00:04:27,932
<i>On any given day,</i>
<i>just one whiff from one of the soup shops</i>

42
00:04:28,034 --> 00:04:30,338
<i>was almost like
having a full meal.</i>

43
00:04:30,981 --> 00:04:33,800
<i>But on one very
special day every year,</i>

44
00:04:33,865 --> 00:04:36,713
<i>the kingdom of Dor</i>
<i>was magically transformed.</i>

45
00:04:39,278 --> 00:04:41,188
<i>In Dor, Christmas was nothing.</i>

46
00:04:41,295 --> 00:04:42,791
<i>Well, they still celebrated it,</i>

47
00:04:42,897 --> 00:04:45,485
<i>but it was nothing
compared to Soup Day.</i>

48
00:04:50,330 --> 00:04:51,311
Watch it, watch it.

49
00:04:51,417 --> 00:04:53,209
Incoming potatoes!

50
00:04:53,308 --> 00:04:54,969
Hurry! Hurry! Excuse us.

51
00:04:55,071 --> 00:04:58,008
<i>Every Dorian, young and old,</i>
<i>would flock toward the castle</i>

52
00:04:58,113 --> 00:05:01,018
<i>because they knew that,
at that very moment,</i>

53
