Oh, it moved! My soup moved!

133
00:10:25,016 --> 00:10:27,123
No, it isn't... It did not move.

134
00:10:27,771 --> 00:10:28,918
Oh, Your Highness.

135
00:10:29,020 --> 00:10:30,036
- Ahhh!
- Darling?

136
00:10:30,143 --> 00:10:33,014
Oh! A rat! There's a rat in my soup!

137
00:10:33,090 --> 00:10:34,652
Madam, I know that this is unfortunate.

138
00:10:34,755 --> 00:10:36,828
And I know that
while on first glance, I might...

139
00:10:36,899 --> 00:10:38,942
- A rat! In my soup!
- No. Please. Shh, shh, shh.

140
00:10:39,014 --> 00:10:41,023
- And I ate it!
- Your Highness, hold on...

141
00:10:42,186 --> 00:10:43,911
- Uh-oh.
- She's right! It's a rat!

142
00:10:45,102 --> 00:10:47,077
- Please...
- Ahhh! It's a rat!

143
00:10:47,919 --> 00:10:50,826
Get me that rat!

144
00:10:51,156 --> 00:10:52,781
Now, I really believe
you're jumping to conclusions.

145
00:10:53,270 --> 00:10:54,701
And I'm sure that the
rats you met last time

146
00:10:54,807 --> 00:10:56,914
might have caused you
to create a stereotype,

147
00:10:57,017 --> 00:10:58,513
but... But I... But...

148
00:10:58,620 --> 00:11:00,761
It's just... I'm just...
I'm not really from around here.

149
00:11:00,861 --> 00:11:02,522
I'm... I'm from... Oh...

150
00:11:02,625 --> 00:11:03,639
Oh!

151
00:11:03,744 --> 00:11:05,120
That's very aggressive.

152
00:11:05,666 --> 00:11:06,683
Get him!

153
00:11:06,789 --> 00:11:07,804
Kitchen...

154
00:11:07,909 --> 00:11:09,120
He's going into the kitchen!

155
00:11:11,369 --> 00:11:12,384
Oh!

156
00:11:17,102 --> 00:11:18,118
Over there!

157
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:20,842
Stop that rat!

158
00:11:21,588 --> 00:11:22,767
Whoa!

159
00:11:23,510 --> 00:11:24,525
I got him!

160
00:11:24,598 --> 00:11:25,646
Uh-oh.

161
00:11:32,287 --> 00:11:34,842
He's going near the soup!

162
00:11:38,052 --> 00:11:39,036
There he is!

163
00:11:39,206 --> 00:11:41,094
lf... If I could just tell...

164
00:11:41,544 --> 00:11:44,329
On the kettle!
That's him, right there!

165
00:11:48,560 --> 00:11:49,542
Look, up there!

166
00:11:59,388 --> 00:12:01,143
Sweetie? Darling?

167
00:12:02,527 --> 00:12:03,989
She's... She's...

168
00:12:05,442 --> 00:12:07,964
She's...

169
00:12:08,645 --> 00:12:11,200
Blimey, she's dead. Get him!

170
00:12:11,304 --> 00:12:12,964
Don't let him escape!

171
00:12:13,065 --> 00:12:15,207
We'll get you, you rowdy rat!

172
00:12:16,748 --> 00:12:17,862
Oh!

173
00:12:21,714 --> 00:12:22,698
No, no, no!

174
00:12:22,772 --> 00:12:24,433
No, not there!

175
00:13:23,636 --> 00:13:25,678
You don't need to be afraid.

176
00:13:26,838 --> 00:13:29,688
I know it's dark,
but you'll get used to it.

177
00:13:30,363 --> 00:13:32,088
Who... Who are you?

178
00:13:32,861 --> 00:13:35,067
Just a rat, like you.

179
00:13:36,674 --> 00:13:38,049
Come with me.

180
00:13:49,998 --> 00:13:53,680
<i>When something hurts
this much, there must be a reason.</i>

181
00:13:54,516 --> 00:13:56,721
<i>There must be someone to blame.</i>

182
00:14:02,940 --> 00:14:05,977
"From this moment on, soup,

183
00:14:06,046 --> 00:14:11,355
"the making of soup,
the selling of soup, or the eating of soup,

184
00:14:11,622 --> 00:14:14,658
"is hereby outlawed
in the kingdom of Dor!

185
00:14:22,353 --> 00:14:25,587
"Rats are to be
considered illegal as well

186
00:14:25,686 --> 00:14:30,162
"and are hereby deemed
unlawful creatures in the kingdom of Dor!

187
00:14:30,233 --> 00:14:31,480
"From this moment on,

188
00:14:31,548 --> 00:14:36,604
"anyone harboring, sheltering
or possessing a rat in any way,

189
00:14:36,673 --> 00:14:39,129
"shall face the full wrath of the law!"

190
00:14:40,421 --> 00:14:42,177
<i>So think about this.</i>

191
00:14:42,245 --> 00:14:46,854
<i>What happens when you make something</i>
<i>illegal that is just a natural part of the world?</i>

192
00:14:48,588 --> 00:14:50,565
<i>You may as well
make flies illegal.</i>

193
00:14:50,671 --> 00:14:52,778
<i>Or sweat. Or Monday morning.</i>

194
00:14:53,649 --> 00:14:56,971
<i>But that's what the King did</i>
<i>out of a terrible sadness.</i>

195
00:15:01,018 --> 00:15:03,508
<i>Sunlight left and
the world went gray.</i>

196
00:15:04,797 --> 00:15:08,664
<i>Colors faded into each other and</i>
<i>dark clouds filled the sky.</i>

197
00:15:10,691 --> 00:15:14,623
<i>And for a long time,
it wouldn't rain.</i>

198
00:15:18,157 --> 00:15:23,880
<i>The clouds just stayed</i>
<i>and stayed and stayed.</i>

199
00:15:33,788 --> 00:15:35,544
I wish it would rain.

200
00:15:36,254 --> 00:15:37,685
You and the whole world, madam.

201
00:15:38,625 --> 00:15:39,608
Ow!

202
00:15:39,714 --> 00:15:40,794
Oh, sorry, milady!

203
00:15:41,444 --> 00:15:43,869
Well, at least I can still feel that.

204
00:15:46,793 --> 00:15:50,659
Louise, do you think
there's a bit of light

205
00:15:51,309 --> 00:15:52,392
somewhere in the world?

206
00:15:52,912 --> 00:15:53,961
Don't know, ma'am.

207
00:15:54,034 --> 00:15:55,596
I think there is.

208
00:15:56,499 --> 00:15:59,054
You just need to know where to find it.

209
00:16:10,722 --> 00:16:13,027
<i>Okay, remember</i>
<i>when we told you how,</i>

210
00:16:13,126 --> 00:16:15,877
<i>once upon a time,</i>
<i>there was this brave little mouse?</i>

211
00:16:15,945 --> 00:16:19,363
<i>Well, if you know
anything about fairytales,</i>

212
00:16:19,436 --> 00:16:23,466
<i>you know that a
hero doesn't appear</i>

213
00:16:23,568 --> 00:16:25,774
<i>until the world really needs one.</i>

214
00:16:39,168 --> 00:16:40,251
Oh, look out!

215
00:16:40,353 --> 00:16:43,423
Alms for the blind! Alms for the blind!

216
00:17:20,105 --> 00:17:21,285
Excuse me. Excuse me.

217
00:17:21,870 --> 00:17:23,148
Excuse me.

218
00:17:23,600 --> 00:17:24,909
Excuse me.

219
00:17:25,618 --> 00:17:26,993
- Whoa!
- I'm sorry. Sorry.

220
00:17:27,058 --> 00:17:28,238
- Tilling?
- Oh!

221
00:17:28,598 --> 00:17:30,223
Mr. Mayor, hello!

222
00:17:30,325 --> 00:17:31,439
Where are you going?

223
00:17:31,512 --> 00:17:35,192
Oh, well,
my baby is having a...

224
00:17:35,290 --> 00:17:38,262
No, my wife is having a...

225
00:17:38,399 --> 00:17:40,406
Oh, right. Congratulations.

226
00:17:40,673 --> 00:17:41,951
Thank you. Thank you, sir.

227
00:17:42,531 --> 00:17:44,770
I'm sorry, I... I really... Goodbye.

228
00:17:53,423 --> 00:17:55,018
His eyes are open.

229
00:17:55,089 --> 00:17:56,430
Don't worry about it.

230
00:17:56,497 --> 00:17:58,125
Sometimes they are.

231
00:17:58,228 --> 00:17:59,692
But he isn't cowering.

232
00:17:59,799 --> 00:18:01,555
He's looking right at us.

233
00:18:01,624 --> 00:18:03,961
Don't worry. He'll learn to cower.

234
00:18:04,378 --> 00:18:06,071
They all do in time.

235
00:18:06,940 --> 00:18:08,370
But he isn't!

236
00:18:14,950 --> 00:18:19,077
Wow! He's so puny!
And look at those ears!

237
00:18:20,042 --> 00:18:21,450
<i> And, from the very beginning,</i>

238
00:18:21,516 --> 00:18:23,657
<i>Despereaux Tilling heard more,</i>

239
00:18:23,727 --> 00:18:27,374
