241
00:18:45,606 --> 00:18:46,753
Don't look. Don't look!

242
00:18:46,824 --> 00:18:47,871
I won't, I won't.

243
00:18:55,729 --> 00:18:56,712
Mmm.

244
00:18:57,331 --> 00:19:00,080
<i>Despereaux Tilling</i>
<i>had no idea he was small.</i>

245
00:19:01,141 --> 00:19:03,566
<i>He wasn't just small
in human terms.</i>

246
00:19:03,736 --> 00:19:06,106
<i>He was small even for a mouse.</i>

247
00:19:06,812 --> 00:19:09,782
<i>But, to tell you the truth,</i>
<i>he didn't even notice.</i>

248
00:19:10,046 --> 00:19:14,175
<i>In fact, in his own mind,</i>
<i>Despereaux was a giant.</i>

249
00:19:23,630 --> 00:19:25,353
We're worried about him.

250
00:19:25,422 --> 00:19:27,432
He doesn't scurry. He doesn't cower.

251
00:19:27,505 --> 00:19:29,680
At first, we thought he would
grow out of it, but...

252
00:19:29,748 --> 00:19:31,604
Well, he scurries sometimes.

253
00:19:31,669 --> 00:19:32,946
But not when he's scared!

254
00:19:33,046 --> 00:19:34,030
He just does it for fun.

255
00:19:34,137 --> 00:19:35,599
And he never cowers.

256
00:19:35,673 --> 00:19:36,754
We've showed him how, but he...

257
00:19:36,859 --> 00:19:39,251
Well, some kids are slower than others.

258
00:19:39,326 --> 00:19:41,367
He'll cower in time. We'll work on it.

259
00:19:41,439 --> 00:19:43,898
- Yes, but...
- It'll be fine, I promise.

260
00:19:44,579 --> 00:19:46,403
All right, settle down.

261
00:19:46,982 --> 00:19:48,390
Ready, class?

262
00:19:54,062 --> 00:19:55,143
Good.

263
00:19:57,392 --> 00:19:58,824
Mmm! Ah!

264
00:19:59,860 --> 00:20:01,388
Good. Excellent.

265
00:20:11,487 --> 00:20:13,728
- Despereaux!
- Yes?

266
00:20:13,795 --> 00:20:14,843
You didn't cower.

267
00:20:15,460 --> 00:20:16,442
Looks like a sword.

268
00:20:16,516 --> 00:20:18,908
It's a carving knife.

269
00:20:19,976 --> 00:20:22,084
It's beautiful!

270
00:20:22,187 --> 00:20:23,618
It's dangerous.

271
00:20:23,948 --> 00:20:25,861
Do you have anymore?

272
00:20:29,586 --> 00:20:31,498
Despereaux, what are you doing?

273
00:20:31,572 --> 00:20:33,002
We're not even supposed to be here.

274
00:20:33,109 --> 00:20:34,606
That's the dungeon.

275
00:20:34,712 --> 00:20:36,056
They have rats down there.

276
00:20:36,154 --> 00:20:37,584
And they'll eat you.

277
00:20:37,661 --> 00:20:39,483
And pull your arms off!

278
00:20:42,689 --> 00:20:44,314
How far down is it?

279
00:20:45,409 --> 00:20:47,683
I don't know. No one's ever come back.

280
00:20:47,750 --> 00:20:48,959
How come?

281
00:20:49,030 --> 00:20:50,439
'Cause... 'Cause...

282
00:20:50,600 --> 00:20:52,195
'Cause that's where
you go when you get...

283
00:20:52,298 --> 00:20:53,674
When you get...

284
00:20:53,771 --> 00:20:54,918
Banished.

285
00:20:55,886 --> 00:20:57,163
What do you get banished for?

286
00:20:57,455 --> 00:20:58,702
Oh, you know.

287
00:20:58,769 --> 00:20:59,980
- Rules and...
- Breaking.

288
00:21:00,082 --> 00:21:01,294
- We can't even...
- Talk about it...

289
00:21:01,363 --> 00:21:02,412
- Because...
- That's one of the...

290
00:21:03,062 --> 00:21:04,077
Rules!

291
00:21:06,747 --> 00:21:08,058
Despereaux!

292
00:21:09,627 --> 00:21:11,932
I just want to have a quick look.

293
00:21:12,159 --> 00:21:13,918
We got to get out of here!

294
00:21:15,906 --> 00:21:17,052
Oh, gosh.
- Oh, no.

295
00:21:17,156 --> 00:21:18,238
Oh, jeez.

296
00:21:18,310 --> 00:21:19,423
Uh-oh.

297
00:21:33,621 --> 00:21:35,794
Despereaux! You can't feed them.

298
00:21:39,292 --> 00:21:40,699
Hello?

299
00:21:46,498 --> 00:21:49,153
Here you go, whoever you are.

300
00:21:58,320 --> 00:21:59,402
Nice.

301
00:22:32,020 --> 00:22:33,229
You are crazy!

302
00:22:33,299 --> 00:22:34,708
What I say? I said nothing!

303
00:22:34,807 --> 00:22:36,149
Well, you heard exactly what I said.

304
00:22:36,247 --> 00:22:37,743
- I say you crazy.
- No, no, no, no!

305
00:22:53,417 --> 00:22:54,662
Hurry!

306
00:23:07,704 --> 00:23:09,560
Ha! They look hungry, sir.

307
00:23:09,625 --> 00:23:10,838
Mmm-hmm.

308
00:23:13,471 --> 00:23:14,781
Dinnertime.

309
00:23:31,216 --> 00:23:32,778
You're not eating.

310
00:23:32,851 --> 00:23:35,124
Uh, I was.

311
00:23:35,221 --> 00:23:37,459
No, you weren't.

312
00:23:37,527 --> 00:23:40,828
Well, I'm just watching, sir.

313
00:23:41,275 --> 00:23:44,727
Well, that's not very grateful of you

314
00:23:44,832 --> 00:23:47,834
after I've taken you under my wing.

315
00:23:48,162 --> 00:23:52,356
Well, I'm grateful, really.
I am.

316
00:23:52,582 --> 00:23:54,440
You miss something, don't you?

317
00:23:54,504 --> 00:23:56,329
Uh, no, I don't.

318
00:23:56,492 --> 00:23:58,795
There's nothing up there, Roscuro.

319
00:23:59,375 --> 00:24:00,653
Nothing at all.

320
00:24:00,720 --> 00:24:03,089
Oh, no, I know that! Absolutely.

321
00:24:03,410 --> 00:24:05,902
Uh, nothing!

322
00:24:06,518 --> 00:24:08,429
Nothing. Nothing at all.

323
00:24:08,632 --> 00:24:10,064
He's a tough one.

324
00:24:10,170 --> 00:24:12,757
You're not gonna turn him.
Nah, you're not.

325
00:24:12,859 --> 00:24:17,207
Oh, I don't know. A rat is a rat.

326
00:24:17,696 --> 00:24:20,799
It doesn't really matter
where you come from.

327
00:24:49,442 --> 00:24:50,720
I'm sorry.

328
00:25:02,289 --> 00:25:03,720
He is so weird.

329
00:25:03,892 --> 00:25:04,938
No kidding.

330
00:25:05,650 --> 00:25:07,541
That is so beautiful.

331
00:25:07,638 --> 00:25:08,917
I wonder what's out there.

332
00:25:27,019 --> 00:25:29,160
Doesn't scurry.

333
00:25:29,261 --> 00:25:31,170
Didn't cower.

334
00:25:31,245 --> 00:25:32,972
"Didn't cower. Didn't cower.

335
00:25:33,041 --> 00:25:34,449
"Wouldn't scurry."

336
00:25:34,546 --> 00:25:37,898
Oh, here's one:
"Drew pictures of cats on his notebook."

337
00:25:37,974 --> 00:25:39,919
- No! Cats?
- Oh! I can't imagine!

338
00:25:40,249 --> 00:25:43,284
I'm afraid so. Named it Fluffy.

339
00:25:43,900 --> 00:25:47,417
- Oh, I had no idea!
- Oh! That's terrible.

340
00:25:49,539 --> 00:25:51,263
- Despereaux.
- Yes, sir?

341
00:25:51,557 --> 00:25:52,801
Come in, please.

342
00:25:56,650 --> 00:25:58,559
Despereaux, why do you think
you're in school?

343
00:25:59,916 --> 00:26:00,999
To learn?

344
00:26:01,071 --> 00:26:02,118
- To learn, yes.
- Yes.

345
00:26:02,190 --> 00:26:03,205
To learn what?

346
00:26:04,337 --> 00:26:08,979
To learn
how to be a mouse, sir.

347
00:26:09,399 --> 00:26:10,829
That is correct.

348
00:26:10,937 --> 00:26:13,239
And you can't be a mouse if
you don't learn to be afraid.

349
00:26:14,044 --> 00:26:15,705
Oh, Despereaux, this...

350
00:26:15,774 --> 00:26:18,623
There's so many
wonderful things in life to be afraid of

351
00:26:18,688 --> 00:26:20,513
if you'd just learn how scary they are.

352
00:26:20,675 --> 00:26:22,749
Yes. Yes, sir.

353
00:26:26,505 --> 00:26:27,718
How about his brother?

354
00:26:27,786 --> 00:26:29,063
His brother? What about him?

355
00:26:29,163 --> 00:26:31,982
Yes, is he, you know, timid?

356
00:26:32,591 --> 00:26:34,599
Oh! Oh, yes!

357
00:26:34,768 --> 00:26:36,364
- Yes, very timid.
- Yes. So timid!

358
00:26:36,435 --> 00:26:38,096
As timid as the day is long.

359
00:26:38,199 --> 00:26:39,474
Good. Good.

360
00:26:39,669 --> 00:26:42,227
Sometimes they just need
to see the older ones do it.

361
00:26:42,330 --> 00:26:43,793
No one starts out afraid.

362
00:26:44,156 --> 00:26:45,913
- Understood.
- Of course.

363
00:26:46,653 --> 00:26:48,119
- You coddle that boy, that's the problem.
- No.

364
00:26:48,193 --> 00:26:49,208
- Yes, you do.
- No, no.

365
00:26:49,281 --> 00:26:51,224
- Yes, you do. You've been doing it for years.
- He was always...

366
00:26:51,330 --> 00:26:52,315
He's little. I've had to help him.

367
00:26:52,420 --> 00:26:54,973
He's not going to be afraid unless
you allow him to be afraid.

368
00:26:55,045 --> 00:26:56,324
Well, Furlough will teach him.

369
00:27:02,382 --> 00:27:03,365
Do what he does.

370
00:27:03,472 --> 00:27:04,618
And don't do anything he doesn't.

371
00:27:04,689 --> 00:27:06,032
And if he's afraid of something...

372
00:27:06,098 --> 00:27:07,725
Then you need to be afraid of it, too.

373
00:27:27,816 --> 00:27:28,833
Oh!

374
00:27:33,487 --> 00:27:34,536
Wow.

375
00:27:47,581 --> 00:27:49,657
Come on, Furlough, hurry up!

376
00:27:53,509 --> 00:27:54,557
Whoa...

377
00:28:05,457 --> 00:28:08,207
All right, now, you start
nibbling right along that edge there.

378
00:28:09,011 --> 00:28:12,245
The glue is all right,
but it's the pages that taste the best.

379
00:28:12,887 --> 00:28:16,689
Hmm. "Once upon a time."
That's great, isn't it?

380
00:28:17,085 --> 00:28:18,514
"Upon a time."

381
00:28:18,685 --> 00:28:20,544
And they don't even tell you
what time that is yet.

382
00:28:20,609 --> 00:28:22,367
It's like you have to find that out.

383
00:28:22,467 --> 00:28:25,340
You're not supposed to read it, Despereaux.
You're supposed to eat it.

384
00:28:26,663 --> 00:28:28,868
Good. I'll come back in an hour.

385
00:28:29,994 --> 00:28:34,188
And no reading! It's a rule.

386
00:28:47,325 --> 00:28:50,940
<i>Once upon a time,</i>
<i>there lived a fair princess,</i>

387
00:28:51,905 --> 00:28:54,210
<i>fairer than any in any other land.</i>

388
00:28:55,461 --> 00:28:57,056
Hmm. Fair.

389
00:28:57,863 --> 00:29:02,624
<i>And, as the story goes,</i>
<i>she was locked up in a faraway castle,</i>

390
00:29:02,732 --> 00:29:06,051
<i>where she could see the world</i>
<i>but could never touch it.</i>

391
00:29:08,788 --> 00:29:10,676
<i>She longed for a prince.</i>

392
00:29:11,477 --> 00:29:14,449
<i>A brave knight who would</i>
<i>deliver her from all of this.</i>

393
00:29:14,554 --> 00:29:18,299
<i>Someone with courage</i>
<i>and honor and decency.</i>

394
00:29:24,066 --> 00:29:26,109
<i>But in a cruel and
frightened world,</i>

395
00:29:26,214 --> 00:29:28,190
<i>men like this were scarce indeed.</i>

396
00:30:08,401 --> 00:30:10,544
<i>They lived in a special world</i>

397
00:30:11,029 --> 00:30:14,348
<i>built on courage and
chivalry and honor.</i>

398
00:30:14,617 --> 00:30:16,691
<i>They pledged their
lives to each other.</i>

399
00:30:17,115 --> 00:30:20,281
<i>To fight for truth,
to defend the weak,</i>

400
00:30:20,382 --> 00:30:23,963
<i>to seek justice, and to always...</i>

401
00:30:28,455 --> 00:30:29,765
How was the library?

402
00:30:29,864 --> 00:30:30,879
Fine.

403
00:30:31,434 --> 00:30:33,093
Spoil your appetite?

404
00:30:33,421 --> 00:30:35,593
No. Helped it, actually.

405
00:30:36,174 --> 00:30:37,738
Made me hungrier.

406
00:30:39,218 --> 00:30:40,428
Good lad.

407
00:30:43,384 --> 00:30:44,725
Ha-hah!

408
00:30:47,065 --> 00:30:50,417
Did you see they're putting up
a new front on the crumb shop?

409
00:30:50,525 --> 00:30:53,048
Oh! But I loved the old front.
- Quite modern. Yes.

410
00:30:59,624 --> 00:31:01,731
<i>Did a book ever speak to you?</i>

411
00:31:02,058 --> 00:31:04,429
<i>Almost like it was
written for you?</i>

412
00:31:05,101 --> 00:31:06,991
<i>Despereaux loved it all.</i>

413
00:31:07,344 --> 00:31:08,905
<i>Every bit of it.</i>

414
00:31:09,073 --> 00:31:12,304
<i>The truth, the justice,
the bravery,</i>

415
00:31:12,628 --> 00:31:14,290
<i>the sword-fighting.</i>

416
00:31:16,280 --> 00:31:19,001
<i>He even loved things
you wouldn't suspect.</i>

417
00:31:19,997 --> 00:31:22,235
<i>The story said she was a prisoner,</i>

418
00:31:22,302 --> 00:31:24,377
<i>but that wasn't totally true</i>

419
00:31:24,514 --> 00:31:28,292
<i>because she had hope,</i>
<i>and whenever you have hope,</i>

420
00:31:28,358 --> 00:31:30,434
<i>you're never really
anybody's prisoner.</i>

421
00:31:31,050 --> 00:31:33,090
Someday, my prince will come.

422
00:31:33,676 --> 00:31:35,653
<i>But how did she know that?</i>

423
00:31:35,886 --> 00:31:37,926
Yeah, how did she know that?

424
00:32:24,255 --> 00:32:25,664
Why are you crying?

425
00:32:27,973 --> 00:32:29,696
Why are you crying?

426
00:32:31,142 --> 00:32:32,705
Down here.

427
00:32:32,968 --> 00:32:34,246
Are you a rat?

428
00:32:34,635 --> 00:32:35,617
No.

429
00:32:35,692 --> 00:32:37,287
What are you? A mouse?

430
00:32:40,143 --> 00:32:41,552
I am a gentleman.

431
00:32:44,406 --> 00:32:45,867
And how do you do?

432
00:32:48,249 --> 00:32:49,232
You're sad.

433
00:32:50,044 --> 00:32:51,059
Yes.

434
00:32:51,357 --> 00:32:52,405
Because you have longing.

435
00:32:54,561 --> 00:32:55,988
You're a strange little mouse.

436
00:32:56,769 --> 00:32:57,753
Thank you.

437
00:33:01,318 --> 00:33:02,531
Come on.

438
00:33:10,290 --> 00:33:11,631
Where did you hear that?

439
00:33:12,499 --> 00:33:14,027
About the longing.

440
00:33:14,101 --> 00:33:15,379
In a story.

441
00:33:15,479 --> 00:33:17,421
A story? About what?

442
00:33:17,879 --> 00:33:20,502
About a princess, like you,
in a castle, like this.

443
00:33:21,596 --> 00:33:24,381
Oh. You're a smooth little mouse,
aren't you?

444
00:33:25,601 --> 00:33:27,969
Bet you tell that to all the princesses.

445
00:33:28,354 --> 00:33:30,112
I am sworn to tell the truth.

446
00:33:30,375 --> 00:33:31,749
It is a code of honor.

447
00:33:31,847 --> 00:33:36,392
Ah. Not just a gentleman,
an honorable gentleman.

448
00:33:37,803 --> 00:33:40,393
Well, then, how does this story end

449
00:33:40,496 --> 00:33:42,571
with this princess
who's locked in a castle?

450
00:33:42,643 --> 00:33:44,018
I don't know...

451
00:33:44,308 --> 00:33:45,771
I haven't finished it yet.

452
00:33:46,809 --> 00:33:48,149
I'd love to know.

453
00:33:49,144 --> 00:33:51,034
Oh, I wish it would rain.

454
00:33:51,452 --> 00:33:53,492
I wish there was soup again.

455
00:33:53,661 --> 00:33:55,704
I even wish there were rats!

456
00:33:56,833 --> 00:33:58,493
Will you promise me that?

457
00:33:58,595 --> 00:34:01,019
Will you promise to finish your story
and tell me how it ends?

458
00:34:01,542 --> 00:34:03,910
Yes. It will be my quest.

459
00:34:04,873 --> 00:34:08,106
Your quest! You are a very brave mouse.

460
00:34:14,258 --> 00:34:16,334
Thank you, my good gentleman.

461
00:34:22,363 --> 00:34:23,380
Whoa!

462
00:34:25,887 --> 00:34:26,969
Whoa.

463
00:34:36,106 --> 00:34:37,090
Whoa!

464
00:34:50,392 --> 00:34:53,593
<i>Now, there are</i>
<i>all kinds of princesses.</i>

465
00:34:55,295 --> 00:34:57,118
<i>Some are born that way,</i>

466
00:34:57,215 --> 00:34:58,844
<i>some marry into it,</i>

467
00:34:59,043 --> 00:35:02,526
<i>and some are destined
to be princesses</i>

468
00:35:02,598 --> 00:35:03,975
<i>only in their own minds.</i>

469
00:35:05,611 --> 00:35:07,203
<i>But at one time or another,</i>

470
00:35:07,306 --> 00:35:10,212
<i>every little girl
longs to be a princess.</i>

471
00:35:12,432 --> 00:35:14,026
I'm gonna live right there.

472
00:35:14,129 --> 00:35:16,947
Right up there, near the tippy-top.

473
00:35:18,197 --> 00:35:21,399
Quit your daydreaming
and feed those swine!

474
00:35:22,073 --> 00:35:24,533
Yes, I know. It's gonna be all mine.

475
00:35:25,278 --> 00:35:29,986
No, you deaf little urchin.
I said feed those swine!

476
00:35:33,574 --> 00:35:35,552
<i>Miggery Sow had been</i>
<i>shoveling slop</i>

477
00:35:35,657 --> 00:35:37,633
<i>for as long as she could remember.</i>

478
00:35:37,834 --> 00:35:41,484
<i>Her Uncle Ned had put a shovel in her
hand from the minute she could hold one.</i>

479
00:35:42,255 --> 00:35:44,200
<i>But it turned out all right</i>

480
00:35:44,304 --> 00:35:46,217
<i>because she got on</i>
<i>quite nicely with the pigs.</i>

481
00:35:46,292 --> 00:35:47,701
That's right.

482
00:35:47,990 --> 00:35:51,737
I'm gonna have a special room
just for my dresses

483
00:35:51,995 --> 00:35:55,445
and another whole closet
just for my knickers!

484
00:35:55,583 --> 00:35:59,295
<i>In fact, Miggery Sow could</i>
<i>see her future so clearly.</i>

485
00:35:59,874 --> 00:36:03,872
<i>She could see the tiara, the fancy dresses,</i>
<i>the maids-in-waiting,</i>

486
00:36:04,519 --> 00:36:07,392
<i>and when things got</i>
<i>really bad around the farm,</i>

487
00:36:07,467 --> 00:36:11,694
<i>she could see the moment that she would
finally be delivered from all of this.</i>

488
00:36:12,111 --> 00:36:13,455
Not long now.

489
00:36:13,522 --> 00:36:15,147
I promise you that.

490
00:36:15,571 --> 00:36:20,048
20 for the big ones,
15 for the sow, and 12 for the girl.

491
00:36:20,504 --> 00:36:22,963
15 for the girl, same as the sow.

492
00:36:24,380 --> 00:36:27,864
I told you! I told you
I'd make it to the castle!

493
00:36:27,968 --> 00:36:29,398
Whoa!

494
00:36:30,978 --> 00:36:34,048
<i>So sometimes, it doesn't take much</i>
<i>for your dreams to come true.</i>

495
00:36:34,983 --> 00:36:37,736
<i>You just have to be
able to see it that way.</i>

496
00:36:38,508 --> 00:36:41,859
She was beautiful! Like an angel.

497
00:36:42,350 --> 00:36:43,946
You are crazy.

498
00:36:44,113 --> 00:36:46,668
And she smelled so amazing.

499
00:36:47,251 --> 00:36:48,366
Like a garden.

500
00:36:48,854 --> 00:36:49,837
Despereaux!

501
00:36:49,911 --> 00:36:51,821
You can't talk to a human.

502
00:36:51,928 --> 00:36:53,335
That is the worst thing you can do.

503
00:36:53,401 --> 00:36:55,259
No, it's the best thing I ever did.

504
00:36:55,420 --> 00:36:56,730
They will throw you in the dungeon.

505
00:36:56,797 --> 00:36:58,293
You will get eaten by rats!

506
00:36:58,367 --> 00:36:59,580
It would be worth it.

507
00:37:00,002 --> 00:37:01,890
They could tear at my flesh.

508
00:37:01,987 --> 00:37:03,297
Oh, this is bad.

509
00:37:03,363 --> 00:37:05,702
Oh, and when she held me
in her hand, it was...

510
00:37:06,247 --> 00:37:09,448
It was so soft,
like floating in a pillow.

511
00:37:09,804 --> 00:37:11,179
You know what? I'm worried about you.

512
00:37:11,501 --> 00:37:13,097
That's the point, Furlough.

513
00:37:13,168 --> 00:37:14,893
There's nothing to be afraid of.

514
00:37:14,993 --> 00:37:16,904
Quiet! They will hear you.

515
00:37:16,979 --> 00:37:18,671
Come on. Just try it.

516
00:37:18,933 --> 00:37:21,556
Just for a second, just try being brave.

517
00:37:21,720 --> 00:37:23,476
- Oh!
- And stop cowering!

518
00:37:23,578 --> 00:37:25,753
What's going on in here?

519
00:37:25,820 --> 00:37:30,297
What's all this talk
about princesses and bravery?

520
00:37:31,266 --> 00:37:33,789
Furlough, I want to see you
in my study, right now.

521
00:37:37,194 --> 00:37:39,333
Are you sure?
- That's what he said.

522
00:37:39,401 --> 00:37:41,741
- A real human?
- A princess.

523
00:37:43,341 --> 00:37:44,390
We need to tell them.

524
00:37:44,495 --> 00:37:45,991
We need to tell the Mouse Council.

525
00:37:46,098 --> 00:37:48,304
- But they'll...
- This is bad. This is very bad.

526
00:37:48,372 --> 00:37:51,244
If they find out...
If they find out that they didn't find out...

527
00:37:51,351 --> 00:37:54,255
Oh, then they'll find
out that it was me who...

528
00:37:54,329 --> 00:37:55,378
Oh, no.

529
00:37:55,451 --> 00:37:57,527
But they will send him to the dungeon!

530
00:37:57,919 --> 00:38:00,375
- Oh, he'll get eaten by rats!
- Oh!

531
00:38:00,480 --> 00:38:01,911
No, not if we beg.

532
00:38:01,986 --> 00:38:05,852
If we really beg
and show them that he's changed.

533
00:38:06,246 --> 00:38:07,525
That he's afraid.

534
00:38:07,594 --> 00:38:10,944
That he's afraid,
and he's turned into a real mouse.

535
00:38:11,692 --> 00:38:13,003
Despereaux!

536
00:38:22,200 --> 00:38:24,658
<i>Of course,</i>
<i>destiny is a funny thing.</i>

537
00:38:25,243 --> 00:38:28,728
<i>We go out to meet it,</i>
<i>and we don't always know that we are.</i>

538
00:38:37,896 --> 00:38:39,391
For glory and honor!

539
00:38:39,498 --> 00:38:40,906
Surround him!

540
00:38:57,725 --> 00:38:58,970
Despereaux Tilling.

541
00:39:01,984 --> 00:39:04,738
How long have you been
working on this book?

542
00:39:04,804 --> 00:39:06,716
Hmm... A week?

543
00:39:06,822 --> 00:39:08,964
A week? You've hardly cracked it.

544
00:39:09,770 --> 00:39:11,200
Well, I was...

545
00:39:12,491 --> 00:39:14,217
I just wanted to see how it ends.

546
00:39:24,505 --> 00:39:26,515
Refused training as a mouse.

547
00:39:26,588 --> 00:39:29,907
Refused to respect the will
and guidance of elder mice.

548
00:39:30,334 --> 00:39:33,852
Repeatedly engaged in bold
and un-meek behavior.

549
00:39:33,954 --> 00:39:38,748
Triggered willfully
not less than 17 mousetraps.

550
00:39:39,977 --> 00:39:40,993
Just shameful!

551
00:39:41,099 --> 00:39:43,206
Had personal contact with...

552
00:39:43,884 --> 00:39:44,869
With...

553
00:39:47,762 --> 00:39:48,842
With a human being.

554
00:39:50,773 --> 00:39:52,816
Isn't there something you can do?

555
00:39:52,888 --> 00:39:54,862
Antoinette, stop right now! Stop that.

556
00:39:54,935 --> 00:39:56,344
You have to trust them.

557
00:39:56,409 --> 00:39:57,907
They are the Council.

558
00:39:57,980 --> 00:40:00,086
They're the Council because...

559
00:40:00,349 --> 00:40:02,775
Because they're the Council.

560
00:40:04,354 --> 00:40:05,763
They're the Council.

561
00:40:06,404 --> 00:40:08,065
Is there anything you wish to say
in your defense?

562
00:40:09,033 --> 00:40:12,647
Well, it was a very good story,

563
00:40:13,486 --> 00:40:16,838
and she was a very beautiful princess.

564
00:40:19,475 --> 00:40:21,331
Despereaux Tilling,

565
00:40:21,396 --> 00:40:24,849
our laws are here
to protect us and our way of life.

566
00:40:25,464 --> 00:40:28,852
And when one of our citizens
strays from that way of life,

567
00:40:29,214 --> 00:40:31,386
he becomes a threat to us all.

568
00:40:31,967 --> 00:40:33,793
It's an easy question.

569
00:40:34,658 --> 00:40:36,930
Are you a man or are you a mouse?

570
00:40:39,881 --> 00:40:41,158
And your actions have told us

571
00:40:41,225 --> 00:40:44,130
that you have a great deal
of trouble being a mouse.

572
00:40:45,519 --> 00:40:47,307
It is the judgment of this court

573
00:40:47,407 --> 00:40:49,866
that you should be banished
from these walls forever.

574
00:40:50,515 --> 00:40:54,163
You shall be remanded into the
custody of Hovis, the Threadmaster,

575
00:40:54,231 --> 00:40:57,365
who will prepare you for your
descent into the dungeons of Dor,

576
00:40:57,434 --> 00:41:00,886
from which no mouse
and no light has ever escaped.

577
00:41:12,490 --> 00:41:14,564
- Shh!
- My baby!

578
00:41:14,699 --> 00:41:18,151
Quiet. Be quiet, my dear.
There's nothing to be done.

579
00:41:42,665 --> 00:41:44,040
Come with me.

580
00:41:52,148 --> 00:41:53,460
Stand there.

581
00:42:04,353 --> 00:42:05,368
Red?

582
00:42:05,665 --> 00:42:07,523
Ah, so they tell me.

583
00:42:09,797 --> 00:42:11,687
So you're the brave one.

584
00:42:12,745 --> 00:42:13,828
I guess.

585
00:42:13,932 --> 00:42:16,354
It's good. It'll carry well down there.

586
00:42:18,000 --> 00:42:19,562
Wear it proudly.

587
00:42:20,369 --> 00:42:21,833
There's no shame.

588
00:42:24,566 --> 00:42:25,810
It's time.

589
00:42:28,538 --> 00:42:31,736
It's all right.
They're too scared to come down here.

590
00:42:37,892 --> 00:42:39,103
In there?

591
00:42:39,461 --> 00:42:40,892
I'm afraid so.

592
00:42:42,664 --> 00:42:44,128
Courage, right?

593
00:42:44,235 --> 00:42:45,512
And truth.

594
00:42:46,062 --> 00:42:47,950
- And honor.
- Good.

595
00:42:48,046 --> 00:42:50,506
But especially courage.

596
00:43:01,854 --> 00:43:02,835
I'm ready.

597
00:43:02,941 --> 00:43:04,886
All right, then you need to...

598
00:43:41,255 --> 00:43:42,718
What? Whoa!

599
00:44:36,672 --> 00:44:39,523
Hello? Hello?

600
00:44:42,116 --> 00:44:43,100
Whoa!

601
00:44:46,794 --> 00:44:48,073
Lads, let's go, on the double!

602
00:44:51,760 --> 00:44:52,742
Who is that?

603
00:44:53,297 --> 00:44:54,575
Who goes there?

604
00:44:55,445 --> 00:44:56,656
Who is that?

605
00:44:56,726 --> 00:44:58,189
Despereaux Tilling.

606
00:44:58,294 --> 00:45:00,403
Are you a man or are you a mouse?

607
00:45:02,203 --> 00:45:04,726
I am a gentleman.

608
00:45:05,086 --> 00:45:06,496
Oh.

609
00:45:08,033 --> 00:45:09,528
- It's a mouse.
- I'm hungry.

610
00:45:09,634 --> 00:45:12,540
Shh! Quiet, lads. Patience.

611
00:45:13,830 --> 00:45:16,255
And what makes you a gentleman?

612
00:45:16,746 --> 00:45:17,957
A code...

613
00:45:18,027 --> 00:45:19,272
A code of honor.

614
00:45:20,430 --> 00:45:22,472
You're a strange little
mouse, aren't you?

615
00:45:22,545 --> 00:45:24,912
And where did you find
this code of honor?

616
00:45:25,010 --> 00:45:26,868
Well, in a legend.

617
00:45:26,966 --> 00:45:28,310
A legend that I read.

618
00:45:28,407 --> 00:45:31,029
Fine. Oh, tell me this legend of yours.

619
00:45:31,130 --> 00:45:33,271
I could do with a good story right now.

620
00:45:33,565 --> 00:45:34,840
Well,

621
00:45:34,940 --> 00:45:37,246
it's about a princess and a knight

622
00:45:38,369 --> 00:45:40,280
and his quest to save her honor.

623
00:45:40,738 --> 00:45:43,939
Ah. It was a princess
that took away my soup.

624
00:45:44,424 --> 00:45:45,853
She didn't take it.

625
00:45:45,928 --> 00:45:47,971
In fact, she misses it, too!

626
00:45:49,230 --> 00:45:51,271
How do you know all this, then?

627
00:45:51,343 --> 00:45:52,392
I've seen her.

628
00:45:52,720 --> 00:45:54,381
- Seen her?
- I've talked to her.

629
00:45:54,483 --> 00:45:56,818
- Talked to her?
- That's why they sent me down here.

630
00:45:56,916 --> 00:45:59,125
Mmm-hmm.
And what did this princess tell you

631
00:45:59,193 --> 00:46:00,784
when you had your little audience?

632
00:46:00,887 --> 00:46:02,231
Eh? Eh?

633
00:46:02,330 --> 00:46:04,983
Oh, you must be a royal mouse.
Is that it?

634
00:46:05,436 --> 00:46:08,824
She told me that
she missed the soup and the rain

635
00:46:09,538 --> 00:46:11,362
and, most of all, the sunlight.

636
00:46:12,036 --> 00:46:14,528
And that she just
wanted it all to come back again.

637
00:46:17,802 --> 00:46:19,332
Well, I don't want to
hear your little stories

638
00:46:19,405 --> 00:46:21,261
about princesses and sunshine.

639
00:46:22,191 --> 00:46:23,950
Go tell them to the rats!

640
00:46:30,359 --> 00:46:31,571
All right, boys, come on!

641
00:47:10,498 --> 00:47:11,744
Good crowd, isn't it, sir?

642
00:47:12,325 --> 00:47:14,267
Yes, it is, quite.

643
00:47:14,341 --> 00:47:16,385
Mouse! Mouse!
Mouse! Mouse!

644
00:47:23,087 --> 00:47:26,286
Ah, Roscuro! I'm glad you could make it.

645
00:47:26,353 --> 00:47:28,746
I thought you didn't like the arena.

646
00:47:28,853 --> 00:47:31,856
Huh? Oh! No, no.
It... It's an honor, sir.

647
00:47:32,506 --> 00:47:33,522
Oh!

648
00:47:33,627 --> 00:47:34,771
Good.
- Mmm.

649
00:47:34,938 --> 00:47:36,884
Well, enjoy.

650
00:47:37,310 --> 00:47:40,216
Oh, uh... Thank you.

651
00:47:45,029 --> 00:47:46,918
Let the games begin!

652
00:47:59,734 --> 00:48:02,289
Mouse! Mouse! Mouse!

653
00:48:20,300 --> 00:48:21,282
Come on!

654
00:49:03,063 --> 00:49:04,046
Hold on!

655
00:49:10,142 --> 00:49:12,383
Eat! Eat! Eat!

656
00:49:21,931 --> 00:49:22,914
Wait!

657
00:49:23,246 --> 00:49:26,893
Can I have him?
Can I have this one? Please?

658
00:49:30,387 --> 00:49:31,371
What?

659
00:49:31,766 --> 00:49:34,931
It's just that that one looks tasty.

660
00:49:35,095 --> 00:49:37,620
Well, this is progress.

661
00:49:37,692 --> 00:49:41,690
Perhaps we're starting
to leave the past behind us, eh?

662
00:49:41,792 --> 00:49:44,098
Enjoy, my friend.

663
00:49:44,196 --> 00:49:46,336
Don't leave a morsel.

664
00:49:46,437 --> 00:49:48,644
Oh, I won't.

665
00:49:50,601 --> 00:49:51,584
Pull!

666
00:50:07,259 --> 00:50:09,629
Come on, let's go, buster!

667
00:50:09,982 --> 00:50:12,854
That's it. That's it. You keep moving!

668
00:50:14,851 --> 00:50:17,571
It's okay. Keep walking.

669
00:50:17,830 --> 00:50:21,217
Come on, keep moving! Let's go, come on!

670
00:50:23,146 --> 00:50:24,524
It's right up there.

671
00:50:32,243 --> 00:50:33,840
- Huh?
- Keep walking.

672
00:50:41,183 --> 00:50:42,493
- Oh.
- See that?

673
00:50:43,520 --> 00:50:45,280
Light. Real light.

674
00:50:46,725 --> 00:50:49,093
It's mine, but you can share it.

675
00:50:49,734 --> 00:50:53,568
It isn't much, but there isn't much
anywhere since everything turned gray.

676
00:50:55,533 --> 00:50:57,096
You're not gonna eat me?

677
00:50:57,554 --> 00:50:59,659
No. I don't eat mice.

678
00:50:59,986 --> 00:51:01,363
Then what do you eat?

679
00:51:01,589 --> 00:51:02,670
Crumbs.

680
00:51:02,742 --> 00:51:04,018
When I can find them.

681
00:51:05,464 --> 00:51:07,703
So you are a gentleman.

682
00:51:10,365 --> 00:51:11,861
Tell me that story.

683
00:51:12,769 --> 00:51:14,175
About the Princess.

684
00:51:14,976 --> 00:51:16,769
Tell me what she looked like.

685
00:51:17,318 --> 00:51:19,041
Well, she was...

686
00:51:19,142 --> 00:51:20,353
Was she angry?

687
00:51:20,455 --> 00:51:21,603
No.

688
00:51:21,705 --> 00:51:23,299
No, not at all.

689
00:51:23,371 --> 00:51:26,188
Her heart was full of longing.

690
00:51:27,728 --> 00:51:29,257
What's longing?

691
00:51:31,090 --> 00:51:33,877
<i>And that's</i>
<i>how a friendship is born.</i>

692
00:51:34,584 --> 00:51:38,417
<i>Over the next few weeks, he told Roscuro</i>
<i>everything he knew about loyalty</i>

693
00:51:38,524 --> 00:51:40,760
<i>and honor and
chivalry and courage.</i>

694
00:51:40,829 --> 00:51:44,029
<i>He told him about the Princess,</i>
<i>and where her longing came from.</i>

695
00:51:44,128 --> 00:51:47,809
<i>That she missed the rain and
the soup and even the rats.</i>

696
00:51:49,062 --> 00:51:50,110
Even the rats?

697
00:51:50,824 --> 00:51:54,822
<i>He told him about their</i>
<i>code of honor, about his noble quest,</i>

698
00:51:55,244 --> 00:51:57,451
<i>about duty and loyalty.</i>

699
00:51:57,967 --> 00:52:00,938
<i>And there, in the
darkness of the cellar,</i>

700
00:52:01,011 --> 00:52:05,938
<i>two knights pledged devotion to a
princess who was trapped inside a castle.</i>

701
00:52:07,191 --> 00:52:09,618
<i>Trapped in a life full
of pain and longing.</i>

702
00:52:09,725 --> 00:52:11,548
<i>Even if no one could tell.</i>

703
00:52:15,522 --> 00:52:17,278
Your crown, ma'am.

704
00:52:18,469 --> 00:52:19,518
Oh.

705
00:52:20,519 --> 00:52:22,047
I don't want it today.

706
00:52:22,120 --> 00:52:23,846
But it's beautiful, ma'am.

707
00:52:24,170 --> 00:52:26,246
I know, but I don't want it.

708
00:52:26,318 --> 00:52:28,807
You look so pretty in it, ma'am.

709
00:52:28,879 --> 00:52:30,704
Like a princess.

710
00:52:30,963 --> 00:52:33,833
I know. I am the princess.

711
00:52:34,069 --> 00:52:35,565
Oh, I know, ma'am,

712
00:52:35,671 --> 00:52:39,701
but such a fine princess,
with a little, pretty, glittery...

713
00:52:39,771 --> 00:52:41,333
I don't want it!

714
00:52:41,438 --> 00:52:42,780
All right, Mig?

715
00:52:43,743 --> 00:52:45,305
Very well, ma'am.

716
00:52:45,921 --> 00:52:47,549
Please, take it away.

717
00:53:03,923 --> 00:53:04,906
Princess.

718
00:53:06,006 --> 00:53:07,437
Who's the princess?

719
00:53:08,057 --> 00:53:09,619
I'm a princess.

720
00:53:09,690 --> 00:53:11,547
I'm the princess.

721
00:53:13,310 --> 00:53:17,953
My comb, my hat, my gloves

722
00:53:18,949 --> 00:53:22,783
and my pretty powder

723
00:53:22,857 --> 00:53:25,312
on my pretty princess face.

724
00:53:25,483 --> 00:53:27,558
And what do you think you're doing?

725
00:53:27,630 --> 00:53:28,613
Ma'am!

726
00:53:28,719 --> 00:53:31,175
Where did you get all this?

727
00:53:31,280 --> 00:53:33,038
I just borrowed it, ma'am.

728
00:53:33,106 --> 00:53:34,188
Borrowed it?

729
00:53:34,517 --> 00:53:36,460
I was gonna put them all back.

730
00:53:36,598 --> 00:53:37,877
See that you do!

731
00:53:39,289 --> 00:53:42,042
And you can spend the whole week

732
00:53:42,141 --> 00:53:43,900
taking slop to the dungeon

733
00:53:43,967 --> 00:53:45,976
for your little escapade.

734
00:53:46,850 --> 00:53:48,127
"Princess"!

735
00:53:51,622 --> 00:53:54,407
God! She's the princess.

736
00:53:55,627 --> 00:54:00,072
And now I have to carry the sloppy,
gloppy, stinky stew

737
00:54:00,143 --> 00:54:02,732
down in the damp, dark, dingy...

738
00:54:04,884 --> 00:54:07,122
A person could get
lost forever down here.

739
00:54:09,144 --> 00:54:10,194
Oh!

740
00:54:11,804 --> 00:54:12,786
Din-din.

741
00:54:14,239 --> 00:54:15,222
Slop.

742
00:54:17,536 --> 00:54:21,054
No, don't stop! I said "slop"!

743
00:54:25,802 --> 00:54:28,105
How am I supposed to eat this swill?

744
00:54:29,101 --> 00:54:32,302
Oh, stop that!
I don't have to be putting up with all this!

745
00:54:33,745 --> 00:54:35,373
I serve the Princess.

746
00:54:37,463 --> 00:54:40,018
Right. You serve the Princess.

747
00:54:40,121 --> 00:54:42,907
- That's a bit of a laugh, isn't it?
- I do.

748
00:54:43,005 --> 00:54:45,625
- I bring her tea and...
- Well, I don't want to hear it!

749
00:54:46,464 --> 00:54:48,352
Had me own little princess once.

750
00:54:48,865 --> 00:54:50,045
And now I don't.

751
00:54:50,468 --> 00:54:52,959
Oh. What, you had a princess?

752
00:54:54,792 --> 00:54:55,808
Yeah.

753
00:54:55,882 --> 00:54:58,090
Every dad's got a princess.

754
00:54:58,797 --> 00:55:00,774
<i>Till he stops being a dad,</i>
<i>of course.</i>

755
00:55:03,668 --> 00:55:06,386
Sorry. So, so, sorry!

756
00:55:08,024 --> 00:55:09,845
Oh, well, I've got a real one.

757
00:55:09,943 --> 00:55:12,882
And she's got a tiara and fancy robes,

758
00:55:12,988 --> 00:55:15,609
and she's got shiny bits
all over every frock in her closet.

759
00:55:15,710 --> 00:55:18,464
And I get to see her every single day.

760
00:55:19,523 --> 00:55:21,017
What kind of a quest?

761
00:55:21,124 --> 00:55:22,107
Uh...

762
00:55:22,887 --> 00:55:24,580
To right a terrible wrong.

763
00:55:25,032 --> 00:55:26,922
But who did you wrong?

764
00:55:29,678 --> 00:55:30,661
Okay.

765
00:55:32,176 --> 00:55:34,766
Do you remember when
they banished the rats?

766
00:55:35,284 --> 00:55:36,878
- Sure. Yes.
- Okay.

767
00:55:37,685 --> 00:55:39,575
Well, it wasn't all
the rats they banished.

