1093
01:16:32,025 --> 01:16:33,008
Up there!

1094
01:16:34,973 --> 01:16:35,989
The sun!

1095
01:16:51,599 --> 01:16:53,290
Go on, Despereaux.

1096
01:17:01,368 --> 01:17:05,813
Wait! Wait just a moment! Patience!

1097
01:17:08,510 --> 01:17:11,964
Not just yet.

1098
01:17:18,602 --> 01:17:23,624
The honor is all yours, my friend.

1099
01:17:27,348 --> 01:17:30,132
Eat! Eat! Eat!

1100
01:17:30,390 --> 01:17:32,727
Eat! Eat! Eat!

1101
01:17:38,689 --> 01:17:41,407
<i>Okay, remember</i>
<i>when we said that grief</i>

1102
01:17:41,506 --> 01:17:43,998
<i>was the strongest thing
a person could feel?</i>

1103
01:17:44,102 --> 01:17:45,531
<i>Well, it isn't.</i>

1104
01:17:46,344 --> 01:17:47,775
<i>It's forgiveness.</i>

1105
01:17:48,298 --> 01:17:52,098
<i>Because a single act of
forgiveness can change everything.</i>

1106
01:17:53,295 --> 01:17:54,311
No.

1107
01:17:54,735 --> 01:17:55,751
What?

1108
01:17:55,825 --> 01:17:56,808
No.

1109
01:17:57,299 --> 01:17:59,342
You worthless little...

1110
01:17:59,543 --> 01:18:01,878
Eat! Eat! Eat!

1111
01:18:22,668 --> 01:18:23,653
Help!

1112
01:18:37,404 --> 01:18:39,164
Who let him out?

1113
01:18:46,055 --> 01:18:47,037
Hey, you!

1114
01:18:47,239 --> 01:18:48,223
It's that mouse!

1115
01:18:53,741 --> 01:18:54,725
Get him!

1116
01:19:37,467 --> 01:19:41,781
Ah, if it isn't our brave little knight.

1117
01:19:43,139 --> 01:19:45,049
- I wonder.
- No!

1118
01:19:45,155 --> 01:19:47,941
Should I finish you off myself

1119
01:19:48,039 --> 01:19:51,239
or turn you into cat food?

1120
01:20:00,467 --> 01:20:03,603
Here, kitty, kitty, kitty.

1121
01:20:06,201 --> 01:20:10,069
What is that?

1122
01:20:42,047 --> 01:20:44,669
Please. Nice kitty?

1123
01:20:46,406 --> 01:20:47,682
No, no, no, no!

1124
01:20:57,742 --> 01:20:58,758
Hmm?

1125
01:21:32,853 --> 01:21:35,243
Thank you, my good gentleman.

1126
01:21:46,498 --> 01:21:48,062
I am sorry.

1127
01:21:50,950 --> 01:21:53,256
I'm the one who should be sorry.

1128
01:21:56,237 --> 01:22:00,846
I'm so, so sorry.
You've no idea how sorry I am.

1129
01:22:01,842 --> 01:22:03,154
That's all right.

1130
01:22:09,692 --> 01:22:11,187
I'm so sorry.

1131
01:22:17,827 --> 01:22:19,804
<i>So, you could call all of this</i>

1132
01:22:19,910 --> 01:22:22,246
<i>a big misunderstanding
if you wanted to.</i>

1133
01:22:22,344 --> 01:22:25,513
<i>A king was hurt, so he hurt a rat.</i>

1134
01:22:25,581 --> 01:22:28,301
<i>And a rat was hurt,
so he hurt a princess.</i>

1135
01:22:29,297 --> 01:22:32,299
<i>And a princess was hurt,</i>
<i>so she hurt a servant girl,</i>

1136
01:22:32,404 --> 01:22:34,795
<i>without even meaning to do it.</i>

1137
01:22:34,870 --> 01:22:37,687
<i>And that servant had been</i>
<i>hurting for so long,</i>

1138
01:22:37,752 --> 01:22:40,723
<i>that almost nothing</i>
<i>could make her feel better.</i>

1139
01:22:41,885 --> 01:22:46,397
<i>But was it a mistake</i>
<i>or was it just good luck?</i>

1140
01:22:46,883 --> 01:22:49,406
<i>Because the servant girl</i>
<i>went back to her farm.</i>

1141
01:22:49,477 --> 01:22:51,935
<i>And the jailer finally
found his princess.</i>

1142
01:22:52,008 --> 01:22:55,010
<i>And the King found something</i>
<i>stronger than grief.</i>

1143
01:22:55,083 --> 01:22:57,607
<i>And the mice finally
got rid of their fear.</i>

1144
01:23:00,144 --> 01:23:03,790
<i>And the people of Dor</i>
<i>lived side by side with their rats.</i>

1145
01:23:04,756 --> 01:23:06,035
<i>All except one.</i>

1146
01:23:06,104 --> 01:23:07,632
<i>Who went back to sea</i>

1147
01:23:07,705 --> 01:23:09,910
<i>and felt a cool
breeze each morning</i>

1148
01:23:09,978 --> 01:23:13,016
<i>and the sun in his
face every afternoon.</i>

1149
01:23:13,120 --> 01:23:17,247
<i>And we'd tell you that they all
